OL,3,CWhy canal remains shut months after
OL,4,Ctoxic chemical spill
OL,6,FA section of a canal which suffered a
OL,7,Ftoxic chemical spill remains closed to
OL,8,Fboats four months on.
OL,10,FThousands of pounds was raised to help
OL,11,Fsupport local wildlife after sodium
OL,12,Fand zinc cyanide damaged a stretch of
OL,13,Fthe canal in Pleck, Walsall.
OL,15,FUp to 4,000 litres of chemicals leaked
OL,16,Finto a 12-mile stretch of the Black
OL,17,FCountry Canal in August. The water
OL,18,Fclosure was put in place to stop the
OL,19,Fdisturbance of silt, which could risk
OL,20,Ffurther pollutants.
